.TH XUBAMP 1 "2026-07-16" "xubamp 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xubamp \- play MP3 and WAV files in a native Wayland player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xubamp
.RI [ skin ]
.RI [ audio-file ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xubamp
is a native Wayland audio player that sends decoded audio to PipeWire and
renders classic Winamp skin archives.
.PP
Arguments are classified by filename extension. The first
.B .wsz
or
.B .zip
argument selects the skin. Every
.B .mp3
and
.B .wav
argument is added to the playlist in command-line order. Unrecognized
arguments are ignored. If no skin is selected, xubamp uses its built-in skin.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XUBAMP_SKIN
Path to a skin archive. A skin argument on the command line takes priority.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the settings file. If unset, xubamp uses
.IR $HOME/.config .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/xubamp/settings.conf
Persistent settings. The fallback path is
.IR $HOME/.config/xubamp/settings.conf .
.SH SEE ALSO
.UR https://github.com/hec-ovi/xubamp
Project repository
.UE
